1
00:00:00,04 --> 00:00:01,08
- [Instructor] Before we get started,

2
00:00:01,08 --> 00:00:03,03
let's cover what you'll need

3
00:00:03,03 --> 00:00:04,06
and what you'll need to know

4
00:00:04,06 --> 00:00:07,06
before starting this course.

5
00:00:07,06 --> 00:00:10,05
To keep things focused on Terraform itself,

6
00:00:10,05 --> 00:00:12,05
all of the exercises for this course

7
00:00:12,05 --> 00:00:14,04
will take place in a web browser

8
00:00:14,04 --> 00:00:16,05
using cloud-based services,

9
00:00:16,05 --> 00:00:20,00
so there's no need for a powerful workstation.

10
00:00:20,00 --> 00:00:22,02
Although we'll be using GitHub in this course

11
00:00:22,02 --> 00:00:24,08
for editing and managing Terraform code,

12
00:00:24,08 --> 00:00:27,02
we'll be sticking to the most basic features,

13
00:00:27,02 --> 00:00:30,08
so you don't really need to know Git to follow along.

14
00:00:30,08 --> 00:00:34,01
Terraform works on many different cloud platforms.

15
00:00:34,01 --> 00:00:35,09
For the exercises in this course,

16
00:00:35,09 --> 00:00:38,04
we'll just use Amazon AWS,

17
00:00:38,04 --> 00:00:40,05
so you'll need an AWS account.

18
00:00:40,05 --> 00:00:45,00
And we may incur some charges beyond the free tier.

19
00:00:45,00 --> 00:00:48,01
It's unlikely that it will be more than a few dollars worth,

20
00:00:48,01 --> 00:00:51,08
and that's only if you let things run for a long time.

21
00:00:51,08 --> 00:00:54,04
You certainly don't need to be an AWS expert

22
00:00:54,04 --> 00:00:56,04
to be successful in this course,

23
00:00:56,04 --> 00:00:58,07
but ideally, you'll have some familiarity

24
00:00:58,07 --> 00:01:01,03
with different types of AWS resources

25
00:01:01,03 --> 00:01:03,08
and how to work with it.

26
00:01:03,08 --> 00:01:06,02
If you're very experienced with another platform,

27
00:01:06,02 --> 00:01:08,00
like Google Cloud or Azure,

28
00:01:08,00 --> 00:01:09,08
you'll probably be fine, as well,

29
00:01:09,08 --> 00:01:12,02
if you're willing to do a little mental translation

30
00:01:12,02 --> 00:01:15,01
between different resources.

31
00:01:15,01 --> 00:01:17,07
Since this course is about Terraform itself,

32
00:01:17,07 --> 00:01:19,04
we're not actually going to be doing much

33
00:01:19,04 --> 00:01:22,06
with the systems and infrastructure that we set up.

34
00:01:22,06 --> 00:01:24,09
That means you don't really need to be an expert

35
00:01:24,09 --> 00:01:27,07
in managing servers for this course.

36
00:01:27,07 --> 00:01:28,09
You should know the basics

37
00:01:28,09 --> 00:01:31,02
of how to work in Windows or Linux.

38
00:01:31,02 --> 00:01:34,01
And we'll get into some basic networking concepts,

39
00:01:34,01 --> 00:01:37,00
so you'll need familiarity there as well.

